description:
UNIPA attended: 
- the national workshop on elasmobranchs in Naples (>100 international scientists); 
- the International Symposium of Ethology in Erice, Italy (50 international scientists); 
- the Shark Experts’ workshop in Tunisia (approx. 20 people in total: fishers, NGOs and government representatives); 
- talk at the FishForum 2024, by FAO-UN and held in Antalya (Türkiye) (>150 scientists, policymakers, and conservation practitioners); 
- speech at WGVul of the GFCM, at the UN-FAO headquarter, in Rome (around 50 scientists and 70 decision makers at regional and EU level)
